subject: New IDI Process
body:
Hi team,
Please refer to the process document link below for the IDI process. I made notes on the document with potential changes and comments regarding the new IDI platform. It's difficult to know the specifics of the NEW process until I or someone else goes through the steps. 
@Andrea Wicks Bowles
 maybe your client will be willing to be a guinea pig! 
Main changes:
Taking the assessment: participant/respondent no longer receives a login link, username and password to take the assessment, instead, they receive an access code link to create an IDI account
Tracking: The IDI tracking spreadsheet currently has columns for username and password, and the respondent is tracked using the username in the old platform. With the NEW platform, I believe we can use the respondent's email for tracking (using guinea pig would help for this detail) 
Inviting respondent to create their IDI account: Use new platform to send emails or send emails manually? If sending an email manually, the invitation email will need to be updated with new process. 
https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/jxcpjef86o0prl456cl2y/IDI-Process-Final-Draft.docx?rlkey=w9ykt9u3wcwwbttfwd9hod1df&st=osqe69uv&dl=0
Thank you,
Kaitlin Nonweiler 
(she/her/hers)
IDI Administrator  
Email: 
k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com

Cc:
 Juri Mansour <j.mansour@lcwmail.com>
Subject:
 Re: GroupM - couple Zoom questions
 
Hi Rebecca! Sounds good to me. 
 
Yes, Zoom has three options- option 2 'attendees need to register for each occurence to attend' Registrants need to register separately for each occurrence to attend. They can only choose one date and time on the registrant page.would fit best as that option only allows a participant to register for a single session only. registrant cancels, they will need to re-register to attend any future sessions. 
2. Registrant cancellations: I did not receive an email saying that you cancelled. I researched it, and it looks like Zoom does NOT send an email to the host when a registrant cancels their registration. The host has to manually check the registrant list within the Zoom web portal to see who has cancelled.

Is LCW able to set up the registration link on the back end such that any given email (participant) can register for a 
single session only
 and is prevented from registering for more multiple sessions? In other words, the person would need to cancel their initial registration in order to register for a different session?
 
I see that when participants get a registration confirmation email there is an option to edit or cancel their registration details, e.g.:
 
Group M would like to know about cancelations as they happen, so they could offer this seat to others. I just canceled my registration to the GroupM TEST meeting and got this screen:
 
Did you get a notification that I canceled? 
 
Thank you very much!

subject: Re: GroupM - couple Zoom questions
body:
Hi Rebecca! Sounds good to me. 
Yes, Zoom has three options- option 2 'attendees need to register for each occurence to attend' Registrants need to register separately for each occurrence to attend. They can only choose one date and time on the registrant page.would fit best as that option only allows a participant to register for a single session only. registrant cancels, they will need to re-register to attend any future sessions. 
2. Registrant cancellations: I did not receive an email saying that you cancelled. I researched it, and it looks like Zoom does NOT send an email to the host when a registrant cancels their registration. The host has to manually check the registrant list within the Zoom web portal to see who has cancelled.

 Rebecca Parrilla <r.parrilla@lcwmail.com>

Hi Kaitlin, thank you so much for your help in finalizing our session scheduling process with Group M. 
 
GroupM will be sending out registration links for eight sessions at a time, just like you did for the test run last week. 
 
We met with them today and they have two additional questions.
 
Is LCW able to set up the registration link on the back end such that any given email (participant) can register for a 
single session only
 and is prevented from registering for more multiple sessions? In other words, the person would need to cancel their initial registration in order to register for a different session?
 
I see that when participants get a registration confirmation email there is an option to edit or cancel their registration details, e.g.:
 
Group M would like to know about cancelations as they happen, so they could offer this seat to others. Do you know if the meeting organizer (in this case it would be me, bc it’d be on my zoom account) is notified participant cancelations as they happen? I just canceled my registration to the GroupM TEST meeting and got this screen:
 
Did you get a notification that I canceled? 
 
Thank you very much!

External:
 
Hi team,
 
Answers for zoom questions below:
 
Can we customize the Zoom registration confirmation email that goes to participants? Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email can be customized. You can customize the email subject, body of the email, and you can add branding. 
 
Can our Zoom automatically send registrants a calendar invitation? And can we customize the text on it for them?
 
Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email typically includes an option to add the session details to a participant's calendar by clicking an "Add to Calendar" button, allowing them to add the event to their calendar. But THEY have to click the button and add it.  And I can change the email contact to someone besides the primary host, even though it's their account the session is made under. 
 
·
                     
How does the reg link work when there are many session dates/times to choose from? Do we give them a different reg link for each session?  A Zoom meeting can have what they call multiple "occurrences." When you select that registration for the occurrences/sessions is required, you get to choose from three options (see below). 
You can set up the registration page to have multiple dates and times for them to choose from. See the example below. No need for a registration page per session. 
 
Please let me know if you have any questions!
 
Thank you, 
 
 
Juri Mansour (She/Her)
Consultant Project Associate
LCW

External:
 
Hi team,
 
Answers for zoom questions below:
 
Can we customize the Zoom registration confirmation email that goes to participants? Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email can be customized. You can customize the email subject, body of the email, and you can add branding. 
 
Can our Zoom automatically send registrants a calendar invitation? And can we customize the text on it for them?
 
Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email typically includes an option to add the session details to a participant's calendar by clicking an "Add to Calendar" button, allowing them to add the event to their calendar. But THEY have to click the button and add it.  And I can change the email contact to someone besides the primary host, even though it's their account the session is made under. 
 
·
                     
How does the reg link work when there are many session dates/times to choose from? Do we give them a different reg link for each session?  A Zoom meeting can have what they call multiple "occurrences." When you select that registration for the occurrences/sessions is required, you get to choose from three options (see below). 
You can set up the registration page to have multiple dates and times for them to choose from. See the example below. No need for a registration page per session. 
 
Please let me know if you have any questions!
 
Thank you, 
 
 
Juri Mansour (She/Her)
Consultant Project Associate
LCW

Subject:
 GroupM Zoom Questions
 
External:
 
Hi team,
 
Answers for zoom questions below:
 
Can we customize the Zoom registration confirmation email that goes to participants? Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email can be customized. You can customize the email subject, body of the email, and you can add branding. 
 
Can our Zoom automatically send registrants a calendar invitation? And can we customize the text on it for them?
 
Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email typically includes an option to add the session details to a participant's calendar by clicking an "Add to Calendar" button, allowing them to add the event to their calendar. But THEY have to click the button and add it.  And I can change the email contact to someone besides the primary host, even though it's their account the session is made under. 
 
·
                     
How does the reg link work when there are many session dates/times to choose from? Do we give them a different reg link for each session?  A Zoom meeting can have what they call multiple "occurrences." When you select that registration for the occurrences/sessions is required, you get to choose from three options (see below). 
You can set up the registration page to have multiple dates and times for them to choose from. See the example below. No need for a registration page per session. 
 
Please let me know if you have any questions!
 
Thank you, 
 
 
Juri Mansour (She/Her)
Consultant Project Associate
LCW

subject: What’s New at Zoom | February 2025 Recap
body:
Learn more about what makes Zoom Docs and AI Companion the perfect match! Dear Valued Customer, As Zoom evolves, we want to help you stay up to date on how the latest products and features can help
 
Learn more about what makes Zoom Docs and AI Companion the perfect match! 
 
Dear Valued Customer,
 
  
As Zoom evolves, we want to help you stay up to date on how the latest products and features can help you work and collaborate better. We’ll outline some highlights below, including opportunities for further learning.
 
  
To get more detailed information about the latest releases, here are a few resources: 
 
Zoom Digital Customer Success Hub
 - This event hub is full of training and information sessions hosted by the Zoom Digital Customer Success team. 
 
What’s New at Zoom blog
 - The blog is a great spot to keep up with Zoom, and the What’s New post is regularly updated with info about new products and features. 
 
Preview notes
 - A list of upcoming features. This page is only available to Zoom account owners and admins; you must sign in to view them.
 
Release notes
 - A complete list of past releases across the Zoom platform. 
 
  
If you have questions about the features and announcements outlined below, please reply directly to this email.
 
 
*Note: Some products and features may not be available to all customers.
 
Events & Training
Navigating legal and privacy challenges in AI implementation
 - 
AI adoption is transforming businesses, but responsible implementation is key to maintaining security, privacy, and compliance. Watch the on-demand recording of Cheree McAlpine, Chief Legal Officer at Zoom, and Hanan Szwarcbord, VP & Chief Security Officer at Micron Technology, as they share best practices for implementing AI within your organization. Szwarcbord discusses how he worked with legal and compliance teams on Micron’s journey to enabling Zoom AI Companion, while McAlpine provides her perspective on AI as a CLO’s standpoint. 
 
Introducing Zoom Workflow Automation
Zoom Workflow Automation is now generally available! Think of how much time you spend on routine work tasks, like sending a weekly check-in message or duplicating information from one application to another. What may seem like a minute here or there can quickly add up when you have more meaningful projects you’d rather get to. Zoom’s new Workflow Automation can help you get that valuable time back.
 
This powerful tool streamlines work across Zoom Workplace and third-party apps, and leverages AI Companion to summarize and provide actionable insights. With it, you can trigger actions, integrate with external tools, and automate responses based on user interactions, such as emoji reactions. For example, you can keep teams aligned and organized by automatically adding AI Companion meeting summaries to a dedicated Zoom Doc that is then shared in a chat channel!
 
Workflow Automation is now available to paid Zoom users at no additional cost during the free trial period. Visit our support pages to learn how to 
enable
 and 
use
 Workflow Automation. Users must be on Zoom Workplace app to version 6.3.10 or higher to access this feature. And click the button below 
for an overview of what Workflow Automation can do for you!
Learn More About Workflow Automation
 
 
 
How Zoom AI Companion Can Help You
The day-to-day work of an IT administrator looks very different from their colleagues in the marketing department, but Zoom AI Companion can help both of these groups work more efficiently — and they aren’t the only ones!
 
 
Whether you’re already a daily AI Companion user or still thinking about taking the leap, we wanted to provide some inspiration to help you find new ways this powerful tool can streamline your daily tasks. Check out these new step-by-step use cases showing AI Companion workflows for users in IT, marketing, sales, HR, product and project management, and much more. Feel free to share this resource with your Zoom end users!
Explore AI Companion Use Cases
 
 
Service Updates
 
Zoom Software Lifecycle Policy -
 While the next regular Software Lifecycle Policy enforcement date is May 3, 2025, Zoom has decided to maintain the current minimum version requirements that were established for the February 1, 2025, enforcement. Please continue to check our 
support article
 for the table of products and corresponding minimum versions. As always, we highly recommend you regularly download and update to the latest version of Zoom software by checking for updates within the Zoom app or by navigating to 
zoom.us/download
 to take advantage of all our latest security and functionality features.
Zoom firewall settings -
 
Zoom is continuously optimizing our global footprint to improve performance and availability for our customers. Customers should not need to perform any active changes provided they are following the guidance as provided in our support article 
“Network Firewall Settings for CRC and Enhanced API Connector.”
 For any questions or concerns, please contact your account team or 
Zoom Support
.
Catch us on social

If you wish to be removed from our email list, 
unsubscribe
 or 
manage your email preferences.

External:
 
 
Hi team,
 
Answers for zoom questions below:
 
Can we customize the Zoom registration confirmation email that goes to participants? Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email can be customized. You can customize the email subject, body of the email, and you can add branding. 
 
Can our Zoom automatically send registrants a calendar invitation? And can we customize the text on it for them?
 
Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email typically includes an option to add the session details to a participant's calendar by clicking an "Add to Calendar" button, allowing them to add the event to their calendar. But THEY have to click the button and add it.  And I can change the email contact to someone besides the primary host, even though it's their account the session is made under. 
 
·
                     
How does the reg link work when there are many session dates/times to choose from? Do we give them a different reg link for each session?  A Zoom meeting can have what they call multiple "occurrences." When you select that registration for the occurrences/sessions is required, you get to choose from three options (see below). 
You can set up the registration page to have multiple dates and times for them to choose from. See the example below. No need for a registration page per session. 
 
Please let me know if you have any questions!
 
Thank you, 
 
 
Juri Mansour (She/Her)
Consultant Project Associate
LCW

Hi team,
 
Answers for zoom questions below:
 
Can we customize the Zoom registration confirmation email that goes to participants? Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email can be customized. You can customize the email subject, body of the email, and you can add branding. 
 
Can our Zoom automatically send registrants a calendar invitation? And can we customize the text on it for them?
 
Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email typically includes an option to add the session details to a participant's calendar by clicking an "Add to Calendar" button, allowing them to add the event to their calendar. But THEY have to click the button and add it.  And I can change the email contact to someone besides the primary host, even though it's their account the session is made under. 
 
·
                     
How does the reg link work when there are many session dates/times to choose from? Do we give them a different reg link for each session?  A Zoom meeting can have what they call multiple "occurrences." When you select that registration for the occurrences/sessions is required, you get to choose from three options (see below). 
You can set up the registration page to have multiple dates and times for them to choose from. See the example below. No need for a registration page per session. 
 
Please let me know if you have any questions!
 
Thank you, 
 
 
Juri Mansour (She/Her)
Consultant Project Associate
LCW

External:
 
 
Hi team,
 
Answers for zoom questions below:
 
Can we customize the Zoom registration confirmation email that goes to participants? Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email can be customized. You can customize the email subject, body of the email, and you can add branding. 
 
Can our Zoom automatically send registrants a calendar invitation? And can we customize the text on it for them?
 
Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email typically includes an option to add the session details to a participant's calendar by clicking an "Add to Calendar" button, allowing them to add the event to their calendar. But THEY have to click the button and add it.  And I can change the email contact to someone besides the primary host, even though it's their account the session is made under. 
 
·
                     
How does the reg link work when there are many session dates/times to choose from? Do we give them a different reg link for each session?  A Zoom meeting can have what they call multiple "occurrences." When you select that registration for the occurrences/sessions is required, you get to choose from three options (see below). 
You can set up the registration page to have multiple dates and times for them to choose from. See the example below. No need for a registration page per session. 
 
Please let me know if you have any questions!
 
Thank you, 
 
 
Juri Mansour (She/Her)
Consultant Project Associate
LCW

subject: Re: GroupM Zoom Registration Questions
body:
Juri, Please see the answers to your questions below. I hope this helps! :) 
Can the Zoom link registration email that will go out after a participant registers be customizable so that it is easy to search in their email? 
Yes, the Zoom registration confirmation email can be customized. You can customize the email subject, body of the email, and you can add branding. 
 
Can we set up calendar invitations with zoom registration? For example, once someone registers is there an option to include the event on their calendar?
 
Yes, the  Zoom registration confirmation email typically includes an option to add the session details to a participant's calendar by clicking an "Add to Calendar" button, allowing them to add the event to their calendar. But THEY have to click the button and add it.  And I can change the email contact to someone besides the primary host, even though its their account the session is made under. 
Since there are multiple sessions happening on multiple days, how does this work with zoom registration? Currently I understand that for zoom registration we get a link that would take the participant to the registration page and then when they register, they get a unique link.
A Zoom meeting can have what they call multiple "occurrences." When you select that registration for the occurances/sessions is required, you get to choose from three options (see below). I think this also answers your last question. 
Can we input multiple dates and times for them to choose on that registration page or will we need to have a registration page for every session? 
Yes, you can set up the registration page to have multiple dates and times for them to choose from. See the example below. No need for a registration page per session. 
-Kaitlin 
From:
 Juri Mansour <j.mansour@lcwmail.com>
Sent:
 Monday, March 3, 2025 10:46 AM
To:
 Kaitlin Nonweiler <k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com>; Rebecca Parrilla <r.parrilla@lcwmail.com>
Subject:
 GroupM Zoom Registration Questions
 
 
Hello Kaitlin,
I was wondering if you could provide clarity on the following questions regarding Zoom invitation set up in the scenario that a client wanted to have registered zoom links:
Can the Zoom link registration  email that will go out after a participant registers be customizaible so that it is easy to search in their email?
Can we set up calendar invitations with zoom registration? For example, once someone registers is there an option to include the event on their calendar?
Since there are multiple sessions happening on multiple days, how does this work with zoom registration? Currently I understand that for zoom registration we get a link that would take the participant to the registration page and then when they register, they get a unique link.
      Can we input multiple dates and times for them to choose on that registration page or will we need to       have a registration page for every session?
Thanks!
Juri Mansour (She/Her)
Consultant Project Associate
LCW

subject: GroupM Zoom Registration Questions
body:
Hello Kaitlin,
I was wondering if you could provide clarity on the following questions regarding Zoom invitation set up in the scenario that a client wanted to have registered zoom links:
Can the Zoom link registration  email that will go out after a participant registers be customizaible so that it is easy to search in their email?
Can we set up calendar invitations with zoom registration? For example, once someone registers is there an option to include the event on their calendar?
Since there are multiple sessions happening on multiple days, how does this work with zoom registration? Currently I understand that for zoom registration we get a link that would take the participant to the registration page and then when they register, they get a unique link.
      Can we input multiple dates and times for them to choose on that registration page or will we need to       have a registration page for every session?
Thanks!
Juri Mansour (She/Her)
Consultant Project Associate
LCW

subject: Re: Question about help with some HR related stuff
body:
Omg I had a typo! I’m so sorry!
It’s $22 per hour. 
Oops :). 
On Feb 28, 2025, at 4:21 PM, Kaitlin Nonweiler <k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com> wrote:
﻿ 
Happy Friday!
Can I take the weekend to think about it? I'll let you know on Monday. 🙂 
-Kaitlin 
From:
 Nicole Barile <n.barile@lcwmail.com>
Sent:
 Friday, February 28, 2025 12:00 PM
To:
 Kaitlin Nonweiler <k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com>
Subject:
 Question about help with some HR related stuff
 
 
Happy Friday Kaitlin!
We need someone to figure out some admin/clerical HR-related stuff. I was just starting to look for someone to do this on UpWork & then thought....maybe you would be interested. The catch is that we are paying less per hour - much less - for this. We are offering $12/hr for this work. 
You would be essentially calling and/or emailing different state agencies to geet more details on things. This is mostly related to state unemployment and workers compensation. 
I've attached a doc that has more details. If you'd be interested, you would work with me, SG, and Alisa to solve this, as most of the time they need accounting or a leadership person to speak to. And we would explain more about what this all means should you be interested 🙂.
I would estimate this all could be completed by end of March.
LMK what you think.
Thank you!

Learn why this is important
 
CAUTION:
 EXTERNAL
 
Learn important strategies to support Neurodivergent team members
Hello Roma
 
Neurodiversity is an important but often overlooked part of workplace inclusion. That’s why on February 20, we’re hosting a webinar called 'An Overview of Neurodiversity in the Workplace'. This is a FREE virtual session focused on what neurodiversity really means and how we can create environments where everyone can thrive.
This conversation goes beyond awareness—we’ll dig into practical workplace strategies and expert insights to help you understand Neurodiversity and recognize hidden barriers that can diminish workplace inclusion.
Join us and hear from professionals who specialize in neurodiversity and inclusive workplace practices.
 
Reserve Your Spot
 
We look forward to sharing this space with you and exploring tangible ways to make a positive impact. If you have any questions, please feel free to reach out.
 
The LCW Team
 
 
 
 
Reserve Your Spot

Hi friends,

https://forms.office.com/r/KugkG5NnZ2

https://forms.office.com/Pages/DesignPageV2.aspx?subpage=design&FormId=QgqkPC3XyUO5LgdAEB2d0_ue_HuVluNLjeZ6GrTTrTtUNEw5RUJINk40TUNSUDNBN0E0WVVUQzE3Ty4u&Token=2ced0bce742f45039b04fd1ee1924a12
 
My process
Consultant sends the Scheduling Template to Kaitlin indicating if an evaluation QR code and link is needed
Kaitlin creates the evaluation form in her Office Microsoft Forms account
Kaitlin sends the consultant an email (see template below) will the QR code and links (Zoom, survey link for client, collaboration link)

Hey you two!
As you both know, today was Larry's last day; however, he will be still leading some trainings through April. In addition, we are onboarding new trainers. Some facilitators may have changed.
I'm writing you both to make sure that since there are a lot of moving parts & trainer have changed/are changing, that everything in the Scoro calendar, in Outlook, and in Zoom are all set up properly. For example, if the trainer has changed from Larry to Rebecca, I want to ensure that Rebecca is set up as the facilitator on all calendars, she has the Zoom link, and she is able to get into Zoom.
I think most of this is for 
@Kaitlin Nonweiler
 to ensure is updated, but I'm emailing you both, as 
@Juri Mansour
 - you may need to update Kaitlin of any changes to facilitators so she can update accordingly on her end.
If you both are on this already, please ignore me 🙂. Otherwise, I'll let you two smart people work it out. I just want to make sure that everyone has what they need & that nothing falls through the cracks.
Thanks so much & happy weekend!
Nicole

subject: Scheduling & Facilitators
body:
Hey you two!
As you both know, today was Larry's last day; however, he will be still leading some trainings through April. In addition, we are onboarding new trainers. Some facilitators may have changed.
I'm writing you both to make sure that since there are a lot of moving parts & trainer have changed/are changing, that everything in the Scoro calendar, in Outlook, and in Zoom are all set up properly. For example, if the trainer has changed from Larry to Rebecca, I want to ensure that Rebecca is set up as the facilitator on all calendars, she has the Zoom link, and she is able to get into Zoom.
I think most of this is for 
@Kaitlin Nonweiler
 to ensure is updated, but I'm emailing you both, as 
@Juri Mansour
 - you may need to update Kaitlin of any changes to facilitators so she can update accordingly on her end.
If you both are on this already, please ignore me 🙂. Otherwise, I'll let you two smart people work it out. I just want to make sure that everyone has what they need & that nothing falls through the cracks.
Thanks so much & happy weekend!
Nicole
Nicole Barile

📅 February 26, 2025

Register now

Creative ways to celebrate Employee Appreciation Day (and beyond)

subject: What’s New at Zoom | January 2025 Recap
body:
In 2025, be more efficient with Zoom’s AI Companion. Dear Valued Customer, As Zoom evolves, we want to help you stay up to date on how the latest products and features can help you work and collaborate
 
In 2025, be more efficient with Zoom’s AI Companion. 
 
Dear Valued Customer,
 
  
As Zoom evolves, we want to help you stay up to date on how the latest products and features can help you work and collaborate better. We’ll outline some highlights below, including opportunities for further learning.
 
  
To get more detailed information about the latest releases, here are a few resources: 
 
Zoom Digital Customer Success Hub
 - This event hub is full of training and information sessions hosted by the Zoom Digital Customer Success team. 
 
What’s New at Zoom blog
 - The blog is a great spot to keep up with Zoom, and the What’s New post is regularly updated with info about new products and features. 
 
Preview notes
 - A list of upcoming features. This page is only available to Zoom account owners and admins; you must sign in to view them.
 
Release notes
 - A complete list of past releases across the Zoom platform. 
 
  
If you have questions about the features and announcements outlined below, please reply directly to this email.
 
 
*Note: Some products and features may not be available to all customers.
 
Events & Training
Zoom Contact Center Insights: Success Stories & New Feature Deep Dives -
 
Register now
 
to learn more about the latest ZCC features and how they can help you streamline your data center operations. 
 
In 2025, be more efficient with Zoom’s AI Companion
 
You may have heard about Zoom’s AI Companion 2.0 when we announced it last year during Zoomtopia. To help you work and collaborate more effectively in 2025, we wanted to take a closer look at this included* tool and how you can implement it within your organization. 
 
Ask AI Companion questions about what has happened in a meeting to quickly catch up!
 
What is AI Companion 2.0?
AI Companion 2.0 is your next-generation AI assistant that surfaces important information in a convenient side panel, helping you prioritize what matters most and providing suggestions to help you stay on top of your work. With this tool, you can: 
 
Use prompt suggestions and generate answers from AI Companion
 via a convenient side panel across Zoom Workplace, including Zoom Meetings, Zoom Team Chat, Zoom Docs, Zoom Calendar, and Zoom Mail. 
 
Expand the context of information.
 
AI Companion helps you stay organized and on top of your day because it has context from your data generated across Zoom Workplace, including your Zoom Meetings and, when connected, information from Microsoft Outlook, Gmail, Google Calendar, and uploaded files from Microsoft Office and Google Docs. AI Companion remembers previous conversations you’ve had within the side panel and interactions from across Zoom Workplace.
 
Generate next steps from a meeting summary
 and, coming soon, AI Companion will be able to automatically turn those next steps into Zoom Tasks to help keep teams aligned and on track to deliver projects on time. Keep an eye out for the release of Zoom Tasks in the near future. 
 
Summarize unread messages within a Zoom Team Chat channel
 to easily stay up to date on team conversations and avoid getting bogged down in unread chats. Within the new home tab, AI Companion will be able to provide users with a list of updates based on unread chats and emails.
 
Recap email threads
 in Zoom Mail
 without having to read every message.
 
 
The AI Companion side panel in the Zoom Workplace app can help answer your questions. Use the prompts or ask your own!
 
How do I manage AI Companion 2.0 for my account?
 
As an account admin or owner, you can control AI Companion features in the Zoom web portal. You can choose to enable or disable AI Companion features for all users on the account or specific groups of users. Individual users can also enable or disable some AI features for their own use, if not locked by an admin at the account or group level. For more details, see our support article on 
how to enable or disable Zoom AI Companion features
.
 
How do I help my users get started?
 
Making sure AI Companion 2.0 is enabled is the first step, but users may need some guidance on how to get the most out of this new tool. We recommend providing them with resources from the 
AI Companion Onboarding Center
.
 
This library is open to all and can be filtered by product and asset type to help you find what you need fast. You can view, download, and share setup guides, demo videos, email templates to introduce your end users to AI Companion, and more. 
 
*Included at no additional cost with the paid services assigned to Zoom user accounts. AI Companion may not be available for all regions and industry verticals.
 
Service Updates
 
Zoom firewall settings -
 
Zoom is continuously optimizing our global footprint to improve performance and availability for our customers. Customers should not need to perform any active changes provided they are following the guidance as provided in our support article 
“Network Firewall Settings for CRC and Enhanced API Connector.”
 For any questions or concerns, please contact your account team or 
Zoom Support
.
 
Catch us on social 
 
You're receiving this email because you are a Zoom customer. 
If you wish to be removed from our email list, 
unsubscribe
 or 
manage your email preferences.

I know there are some of you I will be communicating with for urgent matters (Larry & Kaitlin - about the Feb.11 webinar, Catalina - about your replacement). I will be available for anything urgent - just tell me it's urgent, and I'll respond 
🙂
.
 
So while I'm away, I will be available if you need me 
🙂
.
 
Thanks lovely people!
 
 
Nicole Barile
 
(She/Her)
Chief Operating Officer
LCW

body:

You’re teaching Zumba?? Wow, that’s impressive! 
  Baby’s going to be a dancer!
 
 
 
 
Rebecca M. Parrilla
 
(MBA, Latina, LGBTQ, Mom)
(she/her)

From:
 Kaitlin Nonweiler <k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com> 
Sent:
 Thursday, February 6, 2025 5:40 PM
To:
 Rebecca Parrilla <r.parrilla@lcwmail.com>; Nicole Barile <n.barile@lcwmail.com>
Cc:
 Juri Mansour <j.mansour@lcwmail.com>
Subject:
 Re: Group M evaluation QR code
 
I added a question to the survey (see below) where they select the date from a calendar. I'm not sure we can isolate the responses based on the answer to one question within Microsoft Forms, BUT we can by downloading the excel spreadsheet. Does this look like what you envisioned?
 
Rebecca, I'm feeling good... some lower back pain, but I'm still teaching Zumba twice a week and going to yoga. I will say hello 
👶
Thank you so much for checking in! 
❣
 
 
From:
 Rebecca Parrilla <
r.parrilla@lcwmail.com
>
Sent:
 Thursday, February 6, 2025 2:12 PM
To:
 Kaitlin Nonweiler <
k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com
>; Nicole Barile <
n.barile@lcwmail.com
>
Cc:
 Juri Mansour <
j.mansour@lcwmail.com
>
Subject:
 RE: Group M evaluation QR code
 
 
Thanks so much, KN. Yes, one survey/evaluation for all sessions. 
 
Is there a way for you to insert a question within the survey that asks participants to enter the date of the session they attended
, so we could cut the data by date? Where they select the date from a calendar or a drop down vs. them writing it in? 
 
Thanks again, KN! How are you feeling??? Say hello to baby for me! 
👶🏽🍼
 
 
Rebecca M. Parrilla
 
(MBA, Latina, LGBTQ, Mom)
(she/her)

LCW
 
 
From:
 Kaitlin Nonweiler <
k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com
> 
Sent:
 Wednesday, February 5, 2025 3:34 PM
To:
 Nicole Barile <
n.barile@lcwmail.com
>
Cc:
 Juri Mansour <
j.mansour@lcwmail.com
>; Rebecca Parrilla <
r.parrilla@lcwmail.com
>
Subject:
 Re: Group M evaluation QR code
 
Hi friends, 
 
I've included my process at the bottom on this email. This is the process I follow, unless a consultant chooses to use their own Office Microsoft account to make the survey. 
 
Juri and Rebecca, see the QR code (attached) and the links below for the GroupM sessions. To clarify, you are using just one survey/evaluation for all sessions?
 
Post-Session Survey link to share with client: 
https://forms.office.com/r/KugkG5NnZ2
 
You can access the Post-Session Survey using this link to make changes and view results – you are a collaborator:
https://forms.office.com/Pages/DesignPageV2.aspx?subpage=design&FormId=QgqkPC3XyUO5LgdAEB2d0_ue_HuVluNLjeZ6GrTTrTtUNEw5RUJINk40TUNSUDNBN0E0WVVUQzE3Ty4u&Token=2ced0bce742f45039b04fd1ee1924a12
 
My process
Consultant sends the Scheduling Template to Kaitlin indicating if an evaluation QR code and link is needed
Kaitlin creates the evaluation form in her Office Microsoft Forms account
Kaitlin sends the consultant an email (see template below) will the QR code and links (Zoom, survey link for client, collaboration link)
Hi (consultant) ,
Here are the links and QR code for the Date - Client Name: Session Name 
Zoom Link:
You can access the Post-Session Survey using this link to make changes and view results – you are a collaborator:
Post-Session Survey link to share with client:

 Nicole Barile <
n.barile@lcwmail.com
>

 Wednesday, February 5, 2025 8:38 AM
To:
 Kaitlin Nonweiler <
k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com
>
Cc:
 Juri Mansour <
j.mansour@lcwmail.com
>; Rebecca Parrilla <
r.parrilla@lcwmail.com
>
Subject:
 Group M evaluation QR code
 
 
Good morning Kaitlin!
 
Can you please produce a QR code & link for Juri & RP as a course evaluation for GroupM's sessions? 
 
In addition, can you ensure Juri & RP have regular access to the data in the surveys and the ability to pull reports from the survey at the client's request without having to ask anyone else to pull them?
 
I'd also like to know your process so I understand as well, in case I need to pull a report ever.
 
Thank you!
 
Nicole Barile

Consultant sends the Scheduling Template to Kaitlin indicating if an evaluation QR code and link is needed

subject: Feb.11 webinar update
body:
Hi & Thanks for all of your help this week!
Just wanted to update you that we have made the Feb.11th webinar live. People have been getting emails to sign up, and we've gotten about 20 people signed up so far!
What I'll need from you is your brain in figuring out the best way to send these people the Zoom link.
We had people sign up in HubSpot so we could capture a lot of data.
What I'm wondering now is, what's next?
I can download the registered people as a list I can share with you.
Is it best we simply send them a calendar invite from Outlook.... (not sure if we can Bcc)... OR is it better to have you manually register them in Zoom so they get an email with the Zoom link & then then can choose to add it to their calendar... OR ...???
I'll schedule a time for us on Monday to chat through this. If you can come up with ideas for how best to approach it prior to our call, that would be great. LMK if you have any questions in the meantime.
Thanks!!
Nicole Barile

 Andrea Wicks Bowles <a.wicksbowles@lcwmail.com>; Patricia Coleman <p.coleman@lcwmail.com>; Rebecca Parrilla <r.parrilla@lcwmail.com>; Larry Baker <l.baker@lcwmail.com>; Chuck Adams <c.adams@lcwmail.com>; Catalina De Sanctis <c.desanctis@lcwmail.com>; Kaitlin Nonweiler <k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com>

Subject:
 Upcoming Online Availability Changes
 
 
Hello team,
Today going forward I will be limited in being online on Tuesdays and Fridays with hours being 8-11 am EST. The rest of the days I'll be online from 8am-12pm EST.  Tuesday's schedule is temporary just for the next month. I will let you know if that changes.
I will be flexible on days that client meetings must happen outside of these hours and adjust those days online availability to accommodate those meetings. 
Any one-on-one meetings will be ad hoc. 
As always if you need to reach me regarding an urgent need that cannot wait or be delegated you can reach me on WhatsApp: 703-504-8519
And text at 6572240067.
If you need me to be available online at later times in a day, please reach out to me and I will work with you. 
I am still sick with my respiratory system being mainly affected. I have never been this sick so I would appreciate your patience with me. I am functional though my ability to speak will be limited until I recover more hopefully sooner rather than later. I will reserve my speaking for client meetings and on rest of meetings I will reply in chat unless absolutely necessary to speak.
Thank you for your understanding & patience. And again please reach out to me if you would like to work with me on adjusting my availability for particular days even if it's just one offs.
Juri

body:
Hi All,
As previously communicated, I will be adjusting my hours today to accommodate a couple meetings outside of my Tuesday work hours so I will be logging off at 10am EST to accommodate those meetings.  
Thanks!
Juri Mansour (She/Her)
Consultant Project Associate
LCW
From:
 Juri Mansour
Sent:
 Friday, January 24, 2025 4:05 AM
To:
 Andrea Wicks Bowles <a.wicksbowles@lcwmail.com>; Patricia Coleman <p.coleman@lcwmail.com>; Rebecca Parrilla <r.parrilla@lcwmail.com>; Larry Baker <l.baker@lcwmail.com>; Chuck Adams <c.adams@lcwmail.com>; Catalina De Sanctis <c.desanctis@lcwmail.com>; Kaitlin Nonweiler <k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com>
Cc:
 Nicole Barile <n.barile@lcwmail.com>
Subject:
 Upcoming Online Availability Changes
 
 
Hello team,
Today going forward I will be limited in being online on Tuesdays and Fridays with hours being 8-11 am EST. The rest of the days I'll be online from 8am-12pm EST.  Tuesday's schedule is temporary just for the next month. I will let you know if that changes.
I will be flexible on days that client meetings must happen outside of these hours and adjust those days online availability to accommodate those meetings. 
Any one-on-one meetings will be ad hoc. 
As always if you need to reach me regarding an urgent need that cannot wait or be delegated you can reach me on WhatsApp: 703-504-8519
And text at 6572240067.
If you need me to be available online at later times in a day, please reach out to me and I will work with you. 
I am still sick with my respiratory system being mainly affected. I have never been this sick so I would appreciate your patience with me. I am functional though my ability to speak will be limited until I recover more hopefully sooner rather than later. I will reserve my speaking for client meetings and on rest of meetings I will reply in chat unless absolutely necessary to speak.
Thank you for your understanding & patience. And again please reach out to me if you would like to work with me on adjusting my availability for particular days even if it's just one offs.
Juri

Hi again 🙂.

February 11
 - a topic around Black history month
Larry will facilitate. I've already put a hold on his calendar
February 20
 - topic TBD but will highlight some of our spotlights
Chuck & Andrea will facilitate. I've put a hold on their calendars.
I will add you to the calendar holds. I'm not sure if you are available to assist with technical support, but if you are, great. If not, we should be OK.
I'm working with the people above on the content.
I'm also working with John (the marketing consultant) about having people sign up for the events via our website. I'm not yet sure how to connect that to Zoom registration, but we will figure that out once John sets up the landing pages for the events.

One thing to think about though.... Larry might do a quiz/trivia during his session. I've attached a list of questions just for you to see. We might not use these all.

I think it's too late to figure out how to integrate/use a trivia app & also teach Larry to use it, but I could be wrong. 
What do you think?

Thank you! 
❤️
 I am pretty far along. LOL It will be here before I know it!
 
The Zoom link is under Larry's Zoom account. When I get the list for the rest of the sessions, I can edit the link to create new occurrences. Under this one link, you can have multiple meetings or occurrences with different dates and durations. 
 
Yes, I believe the names in the attendance report come from the participant’s display name that is attached to their video and that they can manually change within the call. I can email Zoom support for more clarification.
I did some research and found this advice...
For the most accurate attendance reports:
Require Authentication: When scheduling your meeting, enable the 'Only authenticated users can join' option. This ensures that participants must log into their Zoom accounts, providing accurate names and emails in the report.
Inform Participants: Remind attendees to log in with their Zoom accounts before joining the meeting.

subject: Looking Back, Moving Forward: 2024 Summary and 2025 Kick-off
body:
Redesigned Team Chat sidebar, plus a look back at 2024! [
https://click.zoom.com/l/84442/2024-07-22/c5fptt/84442/1721653856lVtLOzdS/zm_cs_banner_bloom.png
] [
https://zoom.com
] Dear Valued Customer, In
 
Redesigned Team Chat sidebar, plus a look back at 2024! 
 
Dear Valued Customer,
 
In 2024, Zoom took major steps to unify the working experience through the launch of Workplace and introduction of productivity tools like Zoom Docs. We also introduced a new generation of AI assistant — AI Companion 2.0 — to help you work and collaborate more efficiently and effectively. 
 
Before we dive into a recap of 2024, let’s take a look at how we’re kicking off the new year!
 
*Note: Some products and features may not be available to all customers.
 
New this year: Redesigned flexible Team Chat sidebar
 
When you update to Zoom app version 6.3.6, you may notice the newly redesigned Team Chat sidebar. With the new customizable sidebar, you can easily organize your workspace by choosing which tabs appear with drag and drop, keeping essentials like direct messages and continuous meeting chats just a click away, decluttering notifications with tab-level badging, accessing a full-suite of tabs under “More,” and quickly finding what you need using advanced sorting and filtering. 
Plus, you can use AI Companion to automate everyday busywork so you can stay on top of what matters and get more done by summarizing unread conversations in key tabs like Folders and Starred, generating action items based on a conversation in any channel, searching for topics and files across chats, and composing messages for you — all in one place. 
Check out our 
blog post
 if you want to learn more about what's possible with Team Chat!
Service Updates
 
Zoom Software Lifecycle Policy -
 
We plan to enforce the next round of our Software Lifecycle Policy on February 1, 2025. Please check our 
support article
 for the table of products and corresponding minimum versions. Users who are running an end-of-life version after February 1 will be logged out of their Zoom app (Desktop, Mobile, and VDI) or not be able to join meetings via the Zoom Client until they update. As always, we highly recommend you regularly download and update to the latest version of Zoom software by checking for updates within the Zoom app or by navigating to 
zoom.us/download
 to take advantage of all our latest security and functionality features.
 
Zoom firewall settings -
 
We are starting to route more traffic across our newer data centers. We want to remind customers to please allow Zoom traffic to all subnets located on our 
Zoom Network Firewall
 page, which includes specific sections by Product, for an optimal experience and to avoid any service disruption. Some of the recently added subnets specific to Zoom Phone & Zoom Contact Center are:
 
144.195.0.0/16
 
206.247.0.0/16
 
170.114.0.0/16
 
159.124.0.0/16
 
147.124.96.0/19
 
Highlights from 2024
 
Now that we’ve looked at how we’re kicking off the new year, here are just a few of the many milestones from 2024: 
 
Fast Company names Zoom one of the world’s most innovative companies of 2024
 
-
 Zoom was named to Fast Company’s prestigious list of the World’s Most Innovative Companies of 2024. The list shines a spotlight on businesses that are shaping industry and culture through their innovations. These organizations are setting new standards and achieving remarkable milestones in all sectors of the economy. Alongside the World’s 50 Most Innovative Companies, Fast Company recognizes 606 organizations across 58 sectors and regions.
 
Zoom Compliance Manager launches
 
-
 In the spring of 2024, we launched Zoom Compliance Manager powered by Theta Lake, a new all-in-one offering that provides archiving, eDiscovery, legal hold, and information protection capabilities to help organizations fulfill regulatory requirements and mitigate organizational communications compliance risks across the Zoom platform.
 
Zoom Workplaces launches, weaving AI throughout the experience
 
-
 
In April 2024, we launched Zoom Workplace, our new, AI-powered collaboration platform designed to help your organization reimagine teamwork by streamlining communications, increasing employee engagement, and improving productivity across flexible work. It’s everything you trust and love about Zoom’s core communications products, combined with our employee engagement, spaces, and productivity solutions, all within the Zoom experience, with AI woven throughout. 
 
AI Onboarding Center helps organizations integrate AI Companion
 
-
 Many tasks can be completed more quickly and efficiently with the help of AI Companion, but that doesn’t mean everyone knows how to take advantage of them. To help administrators and employees take advantage of Zoom AI Companion and start changing the way they work, we created a new 
resource hub
 with downloadable, ready-to-share assets for every product that works with Zoom AI Companion.
 
Zoom introduces beta for Workflow Automation, a no-code workflow builder to boost workplace efficiency
 
-
 
Zoom launched the new Workflow Automation in beta, allowing users to increase efficiency and reduce time spent on routine tasks. Workflow Automation helps users build complex workflows across Zoom Workplace and third-party applications so they can spend time on more meaningful work and collaborate more seamlessly with colleagues. 
 
Single-use Zoom Webinars licenses capacity increased to 1 million attendees
 
-
 We made it easier than ever to host an extra-large, high-capacity virtual gathering with our newest offering: single-use Zoom Webinars licenses that accommodate up to 1 million attendees. Ideal for presenting content to large audiences who don’t need to connect their audio and video to one another, Zoom Webinars is built on our easy-to-use, familiar platform that so many customers have come to know and trust. Our flexible and scalable solutions now enable event organizers to host massive, one-time virtual gatherings with relative ease.
 
AI-first Zoom Docs debuts on Zoom Workplace
 
-
 In August 2024, Zoom launched our AI-first collaborative docs solution. Zoom Docs is powered by Zoom AI Companion, and helps drive productivity and seamless collaboration throughout Zoom Workplace. Zoom Docs can help solve critical challenges facing modern workforces, including time wasted on repetitive tasks, information overload, and facilitation of cross-functional alignment. By utilizing Zoom AI Companion to convert meeting outcomes into actionable documents, Zoom Docs can jumpstart content creation and adapt to different individual and team needs to help boost workers’ productivity. 
 
Workvivo named the only preferred migration partner for Workplace from Meta
 
-
 
As Meta prepared to discontinue their Workplace product, they named Workvivo by Zoom as their only preferred migration partner. Meta and Workvivo worked together to provide 
migration tools
 for migrating and Workvivo provided additional migration services at no further cost to support customers’ transition.
 
Zoom recognized as a Customers’ Choice in the Gartner® Peer Insights™
 
-
 Zoom was recognized as a Customers’ Choice in the 2024 Gartner® Peer Insights™ “Voice of the Customer” report for Unified Communications as a Service (UCaaS). According to Gartner, vendors recognized by customers as a Customers’ Choice meet or exceed the market average for Overall Experience and User Interest and Adoption. 
 
Zoom introduces AI Companion 2.0
 
-
 At Zoomtopia 2024, Zoom announced the next generation of Zoom AI Companion, the AI personal assistant that helps users get more done and is available at no additional cost. Since launching in September 2023, AI Companion has been enabled on more than 4 million accounts, helping users with capabilities like meeting summary, meeting questions, chat compose, and more. The next generation of AI Companion continues to help simplify users’ workdays by sorting through the noise and prioritizing what’s most important with high-quality results. 
 
Zoom named a Leader in the 2024 Gartner® Magic Quadrant™(October) Gartner Magic Quadrant
 
-
 
Gartner named Zoom a Leader in the 2024 Gartner® Magic Quadrant™ for Unified Communications as a Service (UCaaS), Worldwide for the fifth time in a row. The UCaaS report evaluated 11 companies in the unified communications space, and Zoom has been recognized as a Leader in this area. Zoom includes enterprise-grade solutions like Zoom AI Companion, Zoom Contact Center, Zoom Team Chat, Zoom Phone, Zoom Meetings, and Workvivo. 
 
Meet the new Zoom
 
-
 Until November 2024, Zoom’s official name was Zoom Video Communications Inc., reflecting the company’s roots in video communications software. While that is still a priority, Zoom is now about so much more than video meetings. We are an AI-first company delivering modern, hybrid work solutions that enable you to collaborate seamlessly. That’s why we have officially dropped “video” from our legal name and are now known simply as Zoom Communications Inc.
 
 
 
Now that we’ve taken a look at the fantastic year of innovation that was 2024, we want to thank you for being a Zoom customer. We look forward to continuing to work with you as we move forward together into 2025!
 
  
Zoom Success Advisor
 
Catch us on social 
 
You're receiving this email because you are a Zoom customer. 
If you wish to be removed from our email list, 
unsubscribe
 or 
manage your email preferences.

subject: Re: Question ab Zoom attendance for GroupM
body:
Thank you! ❤️ I am pretty far along. LOL It will be here before I know it!
The Zoom link is under Larry's Zoom account. When I get the list for the rest of the sessions, I can edit the link to create new occurrences. Under this one link, you can have multiple meetings or occurrences with different dates and durations. 
Yes, I believe the names in the attendance report come from the participant’s display name that is attached to their video and that they can manually change within the call. I can email Zoom support for more clarification.
I did some research and found this advice...
For the most accurate attendance reports:
Require Authentication: When scheduling your meeting, enable the 'Only authenticated users can join' option. This ensures that participants must log into their Zoom accounts, providing accurate names and emails in the report.
Inform Participants: Remind attendees to log in with their Zoom accounts before joining the meeting.

WOW! Congratulations, Kaitlin! And you’re pretty far along LOL 
 That is very excited and I’m super happy for you and your partner. I wish you a noneventful and healthy rest of your pregnancy!
 
About GroupM. They’ve had 21 sessions already but will be scheduling 49 more. See attached for info about dates. They always use the same Zoom meeting link for all the sessions, which is this one: 
https://languageandculture.zoom.us/j/83883220168
 
Juri told me that you help her with pulling attendance reports for these workshops. But I was confused because Juri told me GroupM doesn’t use a registration link.
 
When you say “
if they join with their name”, do you mean the name that is attached to their video and the Participant List when you’re in the meeting? Because if so, I’d like to remind GroupM about this. I’m just trying to get a handle on how they’ve tracked their attendance so far and I don’t want LCW to get dinged if we can’t provide a specific attendee’s name to them. 
 
Also, under whose name/credentials is this Zoom meeting built? Sarah’s? 
 
Thanks again!
 
 
Rebecca M. Parrilla
 
(MBA, Latina, LGBTQ, Mom)

LCW

Hi Rebecca. I'm doing well. I've been telling everyone as I meet with them...I'm 6 months pregnant! Due April 25th. So far, everything is going well. 2025 should be an exciting year! I hope yours is off to a good start! 
 
To capture the participants' email addresses, you have to have a registration link where participants register. Without a registration link, you can still track participant names for attendance report purposes if they join with their name; however, sometimes they don't, it will be a nickname or a number. If we just need names, we/client will need to remind the participants to ensure their names are correct for attendance purposes. 
 
Yes, I can adjust the timeframe in the Zoom meeting link. Can you remind me of the facilitator and the dates of the GroupM Workshop? Do we have a spreadsheet?
 
-Kaitlin

Hi Kaitlin, how are you? I hope your 2025 is off to a good start!
I'm taking over the GroupM relationship from Sarah. Juri and I are preparing for our call with them tomorrow and I have a question.  From my experience with the zoom links for Boston Scientific I thought that in order to track participant names for attendance report purposes, you have to have a registration link where participants register.  But Juri informs me that we don't do that for Group M, we have a single zoom link that they use for all their sessions but somehow we are still able to capture the names of the participants in our attendance reports for GroupM. Could you please help me understand how that works? How are we able to capture participant names If they don't register with their emails?  
Separately, The Group M Workshop is going from two hours to 90 minutes . would you need to adjust the time frame in the zoom meeting link on the back end at all?  Thank you!

https://languageandculture.zoom.us/j/83883220168

When you say “
if they join with their name”, do you mean the name that is attached to their video and the Participant List when you’re in the meeting? Because if so, I’d like to remind GroupM about this. Also, under whose name/credentials is this Zoom meeting built? Sarah’s? 
 
Thanks again!
 
 
Rebecca M. Parrilla

subject: Re: Question ab Zoom attendance for GroupM
body:
Hi Rebecca. I'm doing well. I've been telling everyone as I meet with them...I'm 6 months pregnant! Due April 25th. So far, everything is going well. 2025 should be an exciting year! I hope yours is off to a good start! 
To capture the participants' email addresses, you have to have a registration link where participants register. Without a registration link, you can still track participant names for attendance report purposes if they join with their name; however, sometimes they don't, it will be a nickname or a number. If we just need names, we/client will need to remind the participants to ensure their names are correct for attendance purposes. 
Yes, I can adjust the timeframe in the Zoom meeting link. Can you remind me of the facilitator and the dates of the GroupM Workshop? Do we have a spreadsheet?
-Kaitlin 
From:
 Rebecca Parrilla <r.parrilla@lcwmail.com>
Sent:
 Tuesday, January 14, 2025 3:55 PM
To:
 Kaitlin Nonweiler <k.nonweiler@lcwmail.com>
Subject:
 Question ab Zoom attendance for GroupM
 
 
Hi Kaitlin, how are you? I hope your 2025 is off to a good start!
I'm taking over the GroupM relationship from Sarah. Juri and I are preparing for our call with them tomorrow and I have a question.  From my experience with the zoom links for Boston Scientific I thought that in order to track participant names for attendance report purposes, you have to have a registration link where participants register.  But Juri informs me that we don't do that for Group M, we have a single zoom link that they use for all their sessions but somehow we are still able to capture the names of the participants in our attendance reports for GroupM. Could you please help me understand how that works? How are we able to capture participant names If they don't register with their emails?  
Separately, The Group M Workshop is going from two hours to 90 minutes . would you need to adjust the time frame in the zoom meeting link on the back end at all?  Thank you!
 
Rebecca M. Parrilla
 
(MBA, Latina, LGBTQ, Mom)
(she/her)

subject: Question ab Zoom attendance for GroupM
body:
Hi Kaitlin, how are you? I hope your 2025 is off to a good start!
I'm taking over the GroupM relationship from Sarah. Juri and I are preparing for our call with them tomorrow and I have a question.  From my experience with the zoom links for Boston Scientific I thought that in order to track participant names for attendance report purposes, you have to have a registration link where participants register.  But Juri informs me that we don't do that for Group M, we have a single zoom link that they use for all their sessions but somehow we are still able to capture the names of the participants in our attendance reports for GroupM. Could you please help me understand how that works? How are we able to capture participant names If they don't register with their emails?  
Separately, The Group M Workshop is going from two hours to 90 minutes . would you need to adjust the time frame in the zoom meeting link on the back end at all?  Thank you!
 
Rebecca M. Parrilla
 
(MBA, Latina, LGBTQ, Mom)

subject: RE: Updated Timesheet & process
body:
Hi everyone,
 
Yes, pay dates for everyone will be the 1
st
 and the 15
th
. It has been like this for a while, the change is that the time sheets will now match up with the periods. You’ll be paid for a given time sheet one period after it ends (15-17 days depending on the month). So January 1-15 will be paid on Feb 1, same as salaried.
 
I know that the actual dates you received your payment have been variable in the past, which can cause problems for you, so I’m working on changing processes so that things are more consistent. I will be initiating payments on or before the pay date, and the processing time is usually 2-3 business days. If the pay date falls on a weekend or holiday (like Feb 1
st
), I will process beforehand.
 
Since the 15
th
 is this week and all of you (except Keri) are in the new system now, you’ll be able to see how it works from your end right away. Keri, you will submit your first time sheet this week and your first pay date will be 2/1.
 
Please let me know with any questions about this! Nicole is the approver, but I’m the process owner so I handle all the technical bits and I want to make it as stress-free as possible.
 
SG

subject: Bill pay process update for 2025
body:
Hi everyone! As promised, here is what you need to know about our bill pay process change. We will stop using Bill.com at the end of January, and are switching to QuickBooks Bill Pay (an Intuit brand). This is cheaper for the company, and offers better integration for my work. (Payroll for full-timers is not changing – this affects contractor and vendor payments only.)
 
Part-time and external consultants:
You should have already gotten an email from me and from Intuit to set up your free QuickBooks Money account so you can keep getting ACH payments. I can also input information manually if necessary.
Please be sure you are sending your time sheets/invoices to your approver (Chuck or Nicole) ONLY. They will then send it to me for processing (this prevents confusion and duplicates).
If you have any questions about your pay, please email Accounting or ping me in Teams.
 
Salaried folks who have expenses and get reimbursements: 
Please continue sending your expense reports to Accounting ONLY as normal. Any reimbursements will be added into your paychecks instead of handled separately.
 
If you are an approver of vendor invoices: 
Please send the PDF invoice to 
lcw+expenses@assist.intuit.com
 and copy Accounting. The Intuit address is a bot inside the accounting software, so I need to also have it in my regular email in case it skips important things! 
For questions or reminders about bills, please only email Accounting.
Since it takes a few days minimum to set folks up in the new system, please be sure to send vendor invoices in a timely manner. 
Domestic vendors will get an email from me and Intuit after I get their first bill in the new system to set up their ACH payment account. 
Vendors currently getting international wires, I will email to discuss options. Vendors on PayPal will not have any changes.
 
Any questions or problems, please let me know!
 
“SG” Gluckstein
 
(they/them)
Accountant
LCW
Email: 
accounting@lcwmail.com
PS: LCW will be closed December 24 through January 1. Wishing you Happy Holidays!

subject: RE: Aflac Links and QR Codes
body:
Hi Kaitlin and Happy New Year.
Thanks so much.  This looks great.  There are a few edits to be made (please).  
 
First, for sessions that are delivered more than once, we can use one QRCode.  This way, Aflac counts all the folks who completed the evaluation for each content.  And it is easier for me to analyze at the end of the year.  So for example-  all the 
Fostering Inclusive Leaders 
sessions would have one 
Fostering Inclusive Leadership
 session QRCode (for all the dates).
 
And second, Aflac approved the dates with just 4 changes.  I checked each new date in Outlook, and Larry is available.  
Please update Copass and Larry’s schedule.  Also, not sure I received invites to these sessions
…  I spoke with Gina, and she asked for the following changes.  
How Culture Influences Communication Styles: MOVE From 2/26 – to 4/15 (same time)
